The '''Chief Happiness Officer''' (CHO) in a company is the manager of workers' happiness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/a-la-une/article/2013/04/30/le-bonheur-est-dans-le-ministere_3168707_3208.html|title=Le bonheur est dans le ministère|first=Jean-Pierre|last=Stroobants|date=30 April 2013|work=Le Monde}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leparisien.fr/societe/metier-responsable-du-bonheur-27-01-2017-6624018.php|title='Chief happiness officer', responsable du bonheur en entreprise|date=27 January 2017|work=Le Parisien}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/emploi/article/2017/05/22/manageur-du-bonheur-un-metier-ou-une-mode_5131693_1698637.html|title=Manageur du bonheur : un métier ou une mode ?|first=Camille|last=Thomine|date=22 May 2017|work=Le Monde}}</ref> Probably originating in North America, CHO posts are being created in European and UK companies to ensure workers' welfare needs are met.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/careers/2015/jul/13/if-youre-happy-and-you-know-it-become-a-chief-happiness-officer|title=If you're happy and you know it ... become a chief happiness officer|last=Knowles|first=Vikki|date=2015-07-13|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>
