{{Orphan|date=September 2014}}
'''Julius Muthamia''' (1933/34 – October 7, 2015) was a [[Kenya]]n businessman and former [[politician]] who represented [[Meru, Kenya|Meru]] in the original [[Senate of Kenya]]<ref>[http://www.parliament.go.ke/plone/senate/news/pioneer-senators-to-grace-senate-opening Pioneer Senators to Grace Senate Opening] at the [[Parliament of Kenya]]; published March 2013; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref> from its [[Constitution of Kenya (1963)|establishment in 1963]] until its abolition in 1966; he subsequently served in the [[Parliament of Kenya]],<ref>[http://www.propertykenya.com/news/006948-kibaki-gets-ensnared-in-the-web-of-meru-politics Kibaki Gets Ensnared in The Web of Meru Politics] in [[The Standard (Kenya)|The East African Standard]]; by Maore Ithula; published June 18, 2006; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref> where he was Assistant Minister for Agriculture and Livestock Development<ref>[http://pdf.usaid.gov/pdf_docs/pnabc155.pdf Proceedings of the Fifth Small Ruminant CRSP Workshop (1986)]; archived at the [[United States Agency for International Development]]; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref> in the government of [[Daniel arap Moi]].<!--NOTE - if Mr Muthamia did in fact serve as assistant minister of health, let's see a source that is NOT a mirror of Wikipedia's article on [[Meru, Kenya]], okay? Seriously; I'd really like to see one.-->
He also served as the chairman of the traditional [[Meru people#Njuri Ncheke - The Council of Elders|Njuri Ncheke]] council,<ref>[https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/?articleID=1144023362&pageNo=2&story_title= Uhuru, Kimunya defend Ringera, say Kibaki acted within the law], at ''[[The Standard (Kenya)|The Standard]]''; published September 7, 2009; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref> of the Horticultural Development Authority,<ref>[http://business.highbeam.com/3548/article-1G1-139236952/farmers-want-mango-juice-factory-set-up Farmers Want Mango Juice Factory Set Up], by the Kenya News Agency via [[Africa News Service]] (archived at [[HighBeam Research]]); published November 29, 2005; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref> and of the [[Uchumi Supermarkets|Uchumi]] [[supermarket chain]].<ref>[http://business.highbeam.com/3548/article-1G1-80833077/kirubi-elected-uchumi-supermarkets-chairman Kirubi elected Uchumi Supermarkets chairman]; from [[Africa News Service]] (archived at [[HighBeam Research]]); published December 15, 2001; retrieved August 23, 2013</ref>
Muthamia died at the age of 81 on October 7, 2015.<ref name=Tuko>[http://tuko.co.ke/49494-former-meru-senator-dies.html Former Meru Senator Dies] by Matilda Nzioki, at Tuko.co.ke, published October 7, 2015; retrieved October 8, 2015</ref>
