'''Mehmet Rüştü Başaran''' (born 1946/47) is a Turkish [[billionaire]] businessman, the head of Habas Industrial and Medical Gases Production Industries, one of Turkey's largest steel producers.<ref name="forbes1"/> In 2018, Mehmet Rustu Basaran ranked #1999 on the ''Forbes'' World's Billionaires list, with wealth listed at US $1.1 billion.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/billionaires/list/3/#version:static_header:source</ref>
Habas was founded by his father [[Hamdi Basaran]] in 1956.<ref name="forbes1"/> he is the chairman and part owner of [[Anadolubank]].
Başaran is divorced, and lives in [[Istanbul]], Turkey.<ref name="forbes1"/>
