'''Osamu Nagayama''' (born April 21, 1947) is the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Chugai Pharmaceutical Co.]], one of Japan's largest drug companies.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1OsfymtMnOUC&pg=PA320&dq=Osamu+Nagayama&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qcB6VPWTPKHbsASG8YDwDQ&ved=0CB8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Osamu%20Nagayama&f=false|title=Conflicts of Interest and the Future of Medicine: The United States, France and Japan|publisher=|year=2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yScL0jnOJOwC&pg=PA224&dq=Osamu+Nagayama&hl=en&sa=X&ei=VcF6VIyCDJPhsATtnoGwDA&ved=0CDwQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=Osamu%20Nagayama&f=false|title=Conflict and Change: Foreign Ownership and the Japanese Firm|publisher=Cambridge University Press |author=George Olcott |year=2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2iK8AAAAIAAJ&q=Osamu+Nagayama&dq=Osamu+Nagayama&hl=en&sa=X&ei=VcF6VIyCDJPhsATtnoGwDA&ved=0CFEQ6AEwCQ|title=Volume 173, Issues 1–3|work=Forbes|year=2004}}</ref><ref name=bus>{{cite web|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=688917&ticker=ROG:VX|title=Osamu Nagayama: Executive Profile & Biography |work=Business Week}}</ref><ref name=bloom>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/people/1872195-osamu-nagayama|title=Osamu Nagayama|work=Bloomberg}}</ref><ref name="roche.com4">{{cite web|url=http://www.roche.com/about/governance/executive_committee/executive_commitee-osamu-nagayama.htm|title=Roche – Osamu Nagayama|work=roche.com}}</ref><ref name="chugai-pharm.co.jp1"/>

He is also chairman of the board of directors of [[Sony Corporation]].<ref name=bus/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sony.net/SonyInfo/News/Press/201306/13-075E/|title=Sony Corporation Executive Appointments|publisher=Sony}}</ref>

Nagayama is Japanese.<ref name="roche.com4"/>  He obtained his bachelor's degree from [[Keio University]] in 1971, where he studied in the Faculty of Business and Commerce.<ref name=bloom/><ref name="roche.com4"/> He began his professional career in 1971 at the [[Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan]].<ref name="roche.com4"/> He joined Chugai Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd., in November 1978.<ref name="roche.com4"/><ref name="chugai-pharm.co.jp1">[http://www.chugai-pharm.co.jp/english/ir/pdf/mee080303e.pdf "NOTICE OF CONVOCATION OF THE ANNUAL GENERAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS FOR THE BUSINESS TERM ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2007"]</ref>

Nagayama is a member of the board of directors of the [[International Centre for Missing & Exploited Children]] (ICMEC), a global nonprofit organization that combats [[child sexual exploitation]], [[child pornography]], and [[child abduction]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icmec.org/missingkids/servlet/PageServlet?LanguageCountry=en_X1&PageId=1225|title=ICMEC Board Members|publisher=ICMEC|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703182150/http://www.icmec.org/missingkids/servlet/PageServlet?LanguageCountry=en_X1&PageId=1225|archivedate=2015-07-03|df=}}</ref>

